<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. &#34;Title of Thesis&#34;. Thesis type, University, Year.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Smith, Amelia</span>. 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Thesis">The Influence of Bible Studies on New Zealand Primary School Children, 1945&#45;1982</span>.&#34; 
	<span class="hover" title="Thesis type">Master&#8217;s thesis</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="University">The University of Auckland</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Year">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
If the thesis is available in electronic format, add the web address.
<br><br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Smith, Amelia</span>. 
